The paper discusses the application of reinforcement learning (RL) methods to model gameplay and human motivations, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on understanding human behaviors in interactive environments, which can be categorized under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of inverse RL to model the underlying value structure of players is related to game theory (cs.GT) and social influence (cs.SI).
